description: Deletes automated backups using the DbClusterResourceId value of the source DB cluster or the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the automated backups.

parameters.name: DbClusterResourceId
parameters.description: The identifier for the source DB cluster, which can't be changed and which is unique to an Amazon Web Services Region.

nested_items.name: DBClusterAutomatedBackup
nested_items.description: An automated backup of a DB cluster. It consists of system backups, transaction logs, and the database cluster properties that existed at the time you deleted the source cluster.

nested_items.name: Engine
nested_items.description: The name of the database engine for this automated backup.

nested_items.name: VpcId
nested_items.description: The VPC ID associated with the DB cluster.

nested_items.name: DBClusterAutomatedBackupsArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the automated backups.

nested_items.name: DBClusterIdentifier
nested_items.description: The identifier for the source DB cluster, which can't be changed and which is unique to an Amazon Web Services Region.

nested_items.name: RestoreWindow
nested_items.description: Earliest and latest time an instance can be restored to:

nested_items.name: EarliestTime
nested_items.description: The earliest time you can restore an instance to.

nested_items.name: LatestTime
nested_items.description: The latest time you can restore an instance to.

nested_items.name: MasterUsername
nested_items.description: The master user name of the automated backup.

nested_items.name: DbClusterResourceId
nested_items.description: The resource ID for the source DB cluster, which can't be changed and which is unique to an Amazon Web Services Region.

nested_items.name: Region
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services Region associated with the automated backup.

nested_items.name: LicenseModel
nested_items.description: The license model information for this DB cluster automated backup.

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: A list of status information for an automated backup:
retained - Automated backups for deleted clusters.

nested_items.name: IAMDatabaseAuthenticationEnabled
nested_items.description: Indicates whether mapping of Amazon Web Services Identity and Access Management (IAM) accounts to database accounts is enabled.

nested_items.name: ClusterCreateTime
nested_items.description: The time when the DB cluster was created, in Universal Coordinated Time (UTC).

nested_items.name: StorageEncrypted
nested_items.description: Indicates whether the source DB cluster is encrypted.

nested_items.name: AllocatedStorage
nested_items.description: For all database engines except Amazon Aurora, AllocatedStorage specifies the allocated storage size in gibibytes (GiB). For Aurora, AllocatedStorage always returns 1, because Aurora DB cluster storage size isn't fixed, but instead automatically adjusts as needed.

nested_items.name: EngineVersion
nested_items.description: The version of the database engine for the automated backup.

nested_items.name: DBClusterArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the source DB cluster.

nested_items.name: BackupRetentionPeriod
nested_items.description: The retention period for the automated backups.

nested_items.name: EngineMode
nested_items.description: The engine mode of the database engine for the automated backup.

nested_items.name: AvailabilityZones
nested_items.description: The Availability Zones where instances in the DB cluster can be created. For information on Amazon Web Services Regions and Availability Zones, see Regions and Availability Zones.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: Port
nested_items.description: The port number that the automated backup used for connections.

nested_items.name: KmsKeyId
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services KMS key ID for an automated backup.

nested_items.name: StorageType
nested_items.description: The storage type associated with the DB cluster.

nested_items.name: Iops
nested_items.description: The IOPS (I/O operations per second) value for the automated backup.

nested_items.name: AwsBackupRecoveryPointArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the recovery point in Amazon Web Services Backup.

nested_items.name: StorageThroughput
nested_items.description: The storage throughput for the automated backup. The throughput is automatically set based on the IOPS that you provision, and is not configurable.
